# Enforce LF line endings for all text files on every platform. Windows
# checkouts with core.autocrlf=true otherwise inject CRLF into the working
# tree, which breaks source-contract tests that match on `\n` and the
# byte-for-byte Firefox manifest gate. Committed blobs are already LF; this
# keeps the working tree consistent with them everywhere.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts must stay LF (executable on POSIX CI runners).
*.sh text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize or diff as text.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.zip binary
*.crx binary
*.xpi binary
*.pdf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.otf binary
*.pem binary

# Keep internal planning / research / working docs out of the `git archive`
# source ZIP that ships to AMO reviewers and release consumers. These are not
# build inputs for the extension and must not leak development workflow notes.
docs/research/ export-ignore
.factory/** export-ignore
ROADMAP.md export-ignore
TODO.md export-ignore
COMPLETED.md export-ignore
RESEARCH_REPORT.md export-ignore
RESEARCH_FEATURE_PLAN.md export-ignore
RESEARCH_FEATURE_PLAN_PASS2.md export-ignore
FIREFOX-PORT.md export-ignore
docs/manifest-generation-design.md export-ignore
